  "prompt": "Which programming language should I learn to develop apps like SnapChat?",
  "response": "To develop an app like Snapchat, you'll need to learn multiple technologies:\n\n1. Mobile App Development:\n- iOS: Swift or Objective-C\n- Android: Kotlin or Java\n- Cross-platform: React Native or Flutter\n\n2. Backend Development:\n- Node.js\n- Python (Django or Flask)\n- Java (Spring Boot)\n- Ruby on Rails\n\n3. Database:\n- Firebase\n- MongoDB\n- PostgreSQL\n- MySQL\n\n4. Cloud Services:\n- AWS\n- Google Cloud Platform\n- Azure\n\n5. Real-time Communication:\n- WebSockets\n- WebRTC\n\n6. Additional Skills:\n- REST APIs\n- GraphQL\n- Microservices architecture\n- Scalability principles\n\nRecommended Learning Path:\n1. Choose a mobile platform (iOS/Android)\n2. Learn backend programming\n3. Understand database management\n4. Study cloud services and deployment\n5. Learn real-time communication technologies\n\nFor beginners, I recommend:\n- Mobile: React Native or Flutter\n- Backend: Node.js\n- Database: Firebase\n\nThese technologies provide a good balance of ease of learning and powerful capabilities for building social media apps.",
